  "title": "U vs x graphs - identifying features",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph of a sinusoidal curve in a plane. The values x sub 1, x sub 2, and x sub 3 are indicated on the x axis and vertical dashed lines extend up from each value. The vertical axis is labeled U and the value 2 J is indicated 3 quarters of the way up the vertical axis and a dashed horizontal line extends out to the right through the plane. The curve begins just below value 2 J and it extends out intersecting where value x sub 1 and 2 J meet and it then curves down intersecting value x sub 2 just above the horizontal axis and it then moves back up and to the right and intersects where values x sub 3 and 2 J meet and it then curves slightly down and the right.\" src=\"/images/f14c5941e3deb543fe61a6336f2be394.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A system consists of several objects that interact with each other by conservative forces. One of the objects is free to move only in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-direction, while the other objects are fixed in space. The potential energy of the system as a function of the position of the moveable object is shown. Which of the following statements is true?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mechanical energy of the movable object in the region shown can never be greater than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 joules\"><math alttext=\"2 joules\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mtext>2 J</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> positions of stable equilibrium for the movable object in the region shown.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The speed of the movable object is greatest at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals x sub 2\"><math alttext=\"x equals x sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The acceleration of the movable object will be positive in the region between <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals x sub 2\"><math alttext=\"x equals x sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals x sub 3\"><math alttext=\"x equals x sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
